  "title": "Mood induction in MDD and healthy adolescents",
  "description": "This dataset contains magnetoencephalography (MEG) and structural magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) data from adolescent participants with major depressive disorder and healthy controls during a monetary gambling mood induction task and resting state. The study investigates electrophysiological correlates of mood and reward dynamics in human adolescents through pre-registered analyses of task-based and resting-state neuroimaging data.",
  "methods_description": "MEG data were acquired during a monetary gambling mood induction task (task-mmi3) and a 10-minute resting state scan (task-rest) in the same session. Task-mmi3 data have been preprocessed with marking of bad channels and segments (motion >5mm and/or noise artifacts). Structural MRI scans were defaced with co-registered fiducial coordinates provided in anatomical JSON files.",
